---
import CustomImage from '@/components/CustomImage'
import ImageCarousel from '@/components/ImageCarousel'
import CardCarousel from '@/components/CardCarousel'
import StickyHeader from '@/components/StickyHeader'
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout'

const SITE_TITLE = 'Echolodia TE'
---

<BaseLayout title={SITE_TITLE}>
	<StickyHeader
		title='Echolodia TE'
		buyUrl='https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3080222381'
		buyLabel='Subscribe on the Workshop'
		exploreLabel='Tech Specs'
		exploreUrl='#specs'
	/>
	<div>
		<h1 class='title text-6xl font-bold'>{SITE_TITLE}</h1>
		<h2 class='text-3xl font-medium mt-4 mb-10'>The Limit is Your Imagination</h2>
		<CustomImage
			imagePath='/src/assets/images/stormworks/echolodia-te/hero.jpg'
			altText='The Limit is Your Imagination'
		/>
		<div class='flex justify-center mt-10'>
			<div
				class='w-fit px-4 py-1.5 text-sm rounded-full bg-sky-500 hover:bg-sky-600 text-white font-medium transition-colors'
			>
				<a href='https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3080222381' target='_blank'
					>Subscribe on the Workshop</a
				>
			</div>
		</div>

		<article class='prose prose-xl dark:prose-invert w-full max-w-none mt-8'>
			<h3>A symphony on wheels</h3>
			<p>
				When we first introduced the Echolodia TE, it was designed as a model for those who needed
				more our of their truck. For those who needed the most powerful, the most accessible, and
				the most capable pickup truck. Now, with the all new 5th generation Echolodia TE, we are
				building on top of the incredible Echolodia 2023, and infusing the original promise of the
				TE again in this generation, creating one of the best trucks ever made in Stormworks.
			</p>
			<CustomImage
				imagePath='/src/assets/images/stormworks/echolodia-te/ext.jpg'
				altText='TE on a jump'
			/>

			<h2>Outside</h2>
			<p>
				Just like on the Echolodia 2023, we've refined the colors on Echolodia TE to be more
				pleasing to the eye when driving. The body is now a brand new, gorgeous Dirt Red, a
				fantastic companion to the Dirt Blue body of Echolodia 2023. Inheriting the redesigned
				engine bay to fit more fuel, Echolodia TE can drive for over twice as long without needing
				to refuel - over <strong>100km on a single tank</strong>. Echolodia TE also features the
				ever-popular Echolodia Fifth-wheel Adapter that is present on Echolodia 2023. The Echolodia
				Fifth-wheel adapter allows Echolodia TE to tow huge and heavy fifth-wheels, and with Tow
				Mode on SenCar 5, means Echolodia TE has the highest towing capacity of any released
				Echolodia.
			</p>
			<p>
				A horn lets drivers of Echolodia TE to communicate with others on the road. The redesigned
				electrical interface got a facelift, for easy electrical charging and discharging of
				Echolodia TE.
			</p>
			<CustomImage
				imagePath='/src/assets/images/stormworks/echolodia-te/eng.jpg'
				altText='The powerful new SentyTek T12 Super engine of Echolodia TE'
			/>
			<p>
				The real star of the show is the new engine. A SentyTek T12 Super is the muscle of Echolodia
				TE, a powerful twelve cylinder supercharged modular engine, with incredible torque and high
				speeds. Paired with RECO 1.3, this engine has the capability to do things never before on
				Echolodia, with more than 40% more power than Echolodia TE (2022).
			</p>
			<h2>Inside Magic</h2>
			<p>
				New colors, repositioned instruments, everything about the redesigned cabin of Echolodia TE
				is welcoming. New heaters, maps, radio, it's all here. Plus, with SenCar 5 Mini, Echolodia
				TE is supercharged with the most advanced and best looking car operating system in
				Stormworks. Featuring an advanced dash and massive interactable central display with
				multiple apps to play with, SenCar 5 Mini is the ultimate upgrade for Echolodia TE.
			</p>
			<CustomImage
				imagePath='/src/assets/images/stormworks/echolodia-te/rear.jpg'
				altText='The redesigned interior of Echolodia TE, with rotating 6 seater cabin, and the SenCar 5 dashboard'
			/>

			<h2>SenCar 5</h2>
			<p>
				SenCar 5 is the successor to the powerful car operating system, SenTOS Car 4. SenCar 5
				enhances your car with all new personalization features, a brand new UI, and more. SenCar 5
				features a brand new UI, made from scratch, with as little compromises as possible. SenCar 5
				is designed to take over nearly every element of a car. Built on top of the powerful SenOS
				architecture, it is easier than ever to control a car now.
			</p>
			<CustomImage
				imagePath='/src/assets/images/stormworks/echolodia-te/dash.jpg'
				altText='The SenCar 5 dashboard in Echolodia TE, showing the new UI and apps'
			/>
			<p>
				SenCar 5 features 7 themes to customize your experience with the car to the max. Custom
				currated colors match each theme perfectly, so that they dont contrast eachother. All of
				these settings can be changed from the microcontroller properties menu.
			</p>

			<h2>So much more</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Horn</li>
				<li>Downshift protection</li>
				<li>Shows open doors on dashboard</li>
				<li>Enhanced trip stats</li>
				<li>Low fuel/battery alarms</li>
				<li>Enhanced clutch</li>
				<li>Developer support</li>
				<li>Open source</li>
				<li>More settings</li>
				<li>More "on-the-fly" settings</li>
			</ul>

			<ImageCarousel
				images={[
					{
						path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/echolodia-te/bed.jpg',
						alt: 'Echolodia TE has an openable hatch, great for easy access'
					},
					{
						path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/echolodia-te/bed-2.jpg',
						alt: 'Echolodia TE has a bed full of equipment'
					},
					{
						path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/echolodia-te/hatch.jpg',
						alt: 'Echolodia TE hatch view'
					},
					{
						path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/echolodia-te/rear.jpg',
						alt: 'Echolodia TE rear view'
					},
					{
						path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/echolodia-te/tow.jpg',
						alt: 'Echolodia TE towing setup'
					}
				]}
			/>

			<p>
				<a
					href='https://github.com/SentyFunBall/SW-SenCar-5'
					target='_blank'
					rel='noreferrer'
					class='underline text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 dark:hover:text-blue-300'
					>SenCar 5 Source Code & Dev updates</a
				>
			</p>
			<p>
				<a
					href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-_KnjahEiBI'
					target='_blank'
					rel='noreferrer'
					class='underline text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 dark:hover:text-blue-300'
					>Watch the trailer on YouTube</a
				>
			</p>

			<h2 id='specs'>Specs</h2>
			<table>
				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<th>Engine</th>
						<td>12cyl supercharged 1x1</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<th>Transmission</th>
						<td>5 speed AutoManual</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<th>OS</th>
						<td>SenCar 5 with SiBTaT</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<th>ECU</th>
						<td>RECO 1.3</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<th>Top Speed</th>
						<td>140mph/225kph</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>

			<h2>Micros used</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>SenCar v5.0</li>
				<li>Custom SIBTaT Controller</li>
				<li>RECO v1.3</li>
			</ul>
		</article>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
	import { animate } from 'motion'
	const showAnimations = localStorage.getItem('animations') === 'true'

	if (showAnimations) {
		animate(
			'.title',
			{ y: [80, 0], opacity: [0, 1] },
			{
				duration: 2.5,
				opacity: { duration: 3 },

				offset: [0, 0.55, 0.75]
			}
		)
	}
</script>
